Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. In a large bowl combine hash browns, potato soup, celery soup, sour cream, salt, pepper, milk, onion and bell pepper; mix well. Spoon into prepared pan and sprinkle with parsley, paprika and cheese. Bake in preheated oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.